<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 23 at 7:27PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Charlotte County
through 800 PM EDT...
At 727 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Saxe, or 8 miles south of Charlotte Court House, moving north at 20
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Keysville...
Charlotte Court House...
Drakes Branch...
Madisonville...
Abilene...
Cullen...
and Wylliesburg.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
